## 5. Platform-Specific Attack Surfaces (iOS & macOS)

| Attack Surface | Details |
|----------------|---------|
| `window.webkit.messageHandlers` | Cross-origin reference leak via `window.open()` race condition. Reported to Apple, fix expected Spring 2026. |
| Navigation policy timing | `WKNavigationDelegate` / policy decisions can have timing issues analogous to other WebView platforms; ensure `duck://` and dangerous schemes are rejected consistently. |
| `file://` access | Native fetches (e.g., `URLSession`) accept `file://` scheme, enabling blind local file reads. |
| Notification icon fetcher | `NotificationIconFetcher.swift` fetches arbitrary URLs via native `URLSession` without origin/scheme validation. |
| Special pages message handlers | `specialPages`, `contentScopeScripts`, `subscriptionPages`, `identityTheftRestorationPages`, `printHandler`, `autofill` — all potentially accessible cross-origin. |
| Universal Links | iOS Universal Links can be triggered from special page context; validate end-to-end trust. |
| JavaScript bridge | Native methods exposed to special pages may be accessible via leaked `window.webkit` reference. |

---

## 6. Threat Scenarios

The AI agent should consider these attacker models when evaluating code changes:

1. **Malicious ad iframe** — Attacker code running in an ad context on any website, attempting to exploit message handlers or navigate to special pages.
2. **XSS on duckduckgo.com** — Attacker achieves script execution on the SERP or any DDG subdomain, pivoting to access browser-internal APIs that trust DDG origins.
3. **Compromised third-party script** — A CDN-hosted dependency is compromised, injecting code that targets special page APIs.
4. **Tab-napping** — User has a special page open in one tab; attacker site in another tab obtains a reference and sends messages.
5. **Drive-by exploitation** — Attacker site automatically exploits special page vulnerabilities on page load to exfiltrate history, settings, or tokens.
6. **Phishing enhancement** — Attacker bypasses security interstitials to make phishing pages load without warning.

