## 7. Testing Methodology Checklist

When the AI agent identifies a potentially vulnerable code path, it should recommend testing from this checklist:

### Agent usage

Use this checklist **internally** to decide what to verify or suggest. **Do not** paste the full checklist into pull request comments. If tests are worth mentioning, list at most one to three targeted cases (see [security-agent-instructions.mdc](./security-agent-instructions.mdc)).

### Window Reference & Lifetime

- [ ] Can external sites obtain `window.webkit` references via `window.open()`?
- [ ] Do references persist after navigation?
- [ ] Can `window.open('duck://page', 'targetName')` get references to existing special pages?
- [ ] Are `window.parent`, `window.top`, `window.frames[]` leaking references?

### Navigation Guards

- [ ] Are `meta refresh`, `307/308` redirects, form actions to `duck://` blocked?
- [ ] Is `window.location` manipulation from external sites prevented?
- [ ] Are URL normalization bugs tested (encoding tricks, path traversal)?
- [ ] Are `javascript:` URLs blocked in all navigation handlers?

### Origin & Trust Boundaries

- [ ] Do `duck://` pages have unique, isolated origins (not `null`)?
- [ ] Is `localStorage`/`IndexedDB` scoped per special page or shared?
- [ ] Can `document.domain` be manipulated?
- [ ] Can special pages relax CSP?

### Message Handlers

- [ ] Is origin validated before processing any message?
- [ ] Are sensitive handlers token-protected?
- [ ] Is prototype pollution possible via `Object.assign` / spread on message data?
- [ ] Are type confusion attacks handled (unexpected types in message params)?
- [ ] Is message queue flooding considered (thousands of messages to bypass validation)?

### Framing

- [ ] Can special pages be iframed, embedded, or loaded via `<object>` / `<embed>` / `<portal>`?
- [ ] Is `frame-ancestors` CSP set correctly?
- [ ] Are sandbox attribute bypass paths tested?

### Input Handling

- [ ] Are search/filter inputs sanitized against XSS?
- [ ] Is DOM clobbering considered (IDs shadowing globals)?
- [ ] Is SVG injection tested?

### Data Leakage

- [ ] Can timing attacks infer sensitive data?
- [ ] Do error messages leak internal state or paths?
- [ ] Can service workers intercept `duck://` requests?

### Native Bridge

- [ ] Are native methods exposed only to verified special pages?
- [ ] Are native fetch operations scheme-restricted and origin-validated?
- [ ] Are file-size and timeout limits enforced?

