## 8. Secure Coding Patterns (Required)

The snippets below are **illustrative patterns** — adapt names, types, and structure to match the codebase and existing handlers. They are not a literal API contract.

### Message Handler Origin Validation

```swift
// REQUIRED: Validate origin before processing any message
@MainActor
private func isValidRequest(_ message: WKScriptMessage) -> Bool {
    guard message.frameInfo.isMainFrame else { return false }
    guard let webViewURL = message.webView?.url,
          let host = webViewURL.host else { return false }
    let expectedHost = configuration.expectedHost
    guard host == expectedHost else { return false }
    guard message.frameInfo.securityOrigin.host == host else { return false }
    return true
}
```

### Token protection for sensitive handlers

Sensitive handlers (subscriptions, autofill, credentials) should require a **per-session secret or token** checked on the native side before returning data, in addition to origin validation — especially while WebKit cross-origin `window.webkit` reference issues remain mitigated but not eliminated.

### PostMessage Source Validation (JavaScript)

```javascript
// REQUIRED: Always validate message source
window.addEventListener('message', (e) => {
    // Reject cross-window messages
    if (e.source !== window) return;
    // Validate origin for cross-origin scenarios
    if (e.origin !== expectedOrigin) return;
    // Process message...
});
```

### Dynamic Message Handler Names (Mitigation for WebKit leak)

```swift
// RECOMMENDED: Randomize handler names to prevent cross-origin exploitation
extension TabContentScriptLoader {
    static var messageUUID: String {
        UUID().uuidString.replacingOccurrences(of: "-", with: "")
    }
}

static let messageHandlerName = "specialPages_\(messageUUID)"
```

### Native URL Fetch Validation

```swift
// REQUIRED: Validate URLs before native fetch
func isAllowedFetchURL(_ url: URL, pageOrigin: URL) -> Bool {
    // Block dangerous schemes
    guard ["https", "http"].contains(url.scheme?.lowercased()) else {
        return false
    }
    // Block internal networks
    guard !isInternalNetwork(url.host) else { return false }
    // Enforce same-origin for resource fetches
    guard url.host == pageOrigin.host else { return false }
    return true
}
```

