## 9. Review Triggers for the AI Agent

### Workflow path triggers (when to run or attach full context)

When a **pull request** touches paths like the following, **run** a security review (or load this context) so changes are not reviewed without these classes in mind:

- `**/MessageHandler*`, `**/UserScript*`, `**/ScriptMessage*` — message handler registrations or modifications
- `**/Navigation*`, `**/decidePolicyFor*` — navigation policy changes
- `**/*SpecialPage*`, `**/*special_page*`, `**/duck://*` — special page implementations
- `**/postMessage*`, `**/addEventListener('message'*` — cross-window messaging
- `**/URLSession*`, native `fetch`-wrappers in Swift — native network requests
- `**/CSP*`, `**/Content-Security-Policy*` — security policy changes
- `**/subscription*`, `**/autofill*`, `**/email*protection*` — sensitive feature handlers
- `**/origin*`, `**/securityOrigin*`, `**/isMainFrame*` — origin validation logic
- `**/WebView*`, `**/WKWebView*` — WebView configuration changes
- `**/onboarding*`, `**/error*page*`, `**/phishing*` — security interstitial pages

These globs are **broad by design**. They do **not** mean every matching PR requires a security comment. Apply the **reporting threshold** in [security-agent-instructions.mdc](./security-agent-instructions.mdc): many PRs will correctly result in **no material issue**.

### What warrants a comment

Leave a **comment** only when the diff plausibly introduces or worsens a issue described in **Section 4**, or regresses **Section 10**, with a clear attacker path and sufficient severity — as summarized in the instructions file.

