## 10. Appendix: Known Findings Summary (iOS & macOS)

Cross-platform assessments may track additional issues on other platforms; those are **not listed here**.

| ID | Platform | Finding | Risk | Status |
|----|----------|---------|------|--------|
| F1 | macOS | Cross-Origin Subscription Token Leakage via `window.webkit` race | High | Fixed |
| F3 | macOS | Notification Icon Handler SSRF / Blind File Read via native `URLSession` | Medium | Fixed |
| F4 | macOS, iOS | Special Error Page Bypass (phishing/TLS warnings dismissed via `visitSite`) | Medium | Open |
| F5 | macOS, iOS | Email Protection Cross-Site Logout via unvalidated `postMessage` | Medium | Open |
| F8 | macOS | Onboarding Focus Hijack (DoS via `duck://onboarding` navigation + redirect) | Low | Open |
| F9 | macOS | Message Handler Serialization Crash (throwing getter in message payload) | Low | Open |
| F0 | macOS | History Page XSS via unsanitized `javascript:` URL in open handler (incident) | High | Fixed |

### Root Cause Dependency

- **Apple/WebKit:** Cross-origin `window.webkit` reference leak — reported to Apple, fix expected Spring 2026. Mitigation: dynamic message handler names + origin validation + token protection for sensitive handlers.

